---
import Layout from '../../layouts/ProjectPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Opportunities for K-12 Students"
	description="Discover exciting robotics programs designed to spark your curiosity and develop valuable skills in technology and engineering."
	pubDate={new Date('January 01 2023')}
	heroImage={undefined}
>
	<div class="content-page">
		<header class="page-header">
			<h1>Opportunities for K-12 Students</h1>
			<p class="page-description">
				Discover exciting robotics programs designed to spark your curiosity and develop valuable skills in technology and engineering.
			</p>
		</header>

		<section class="content-section">
			<p class="lead-text">
				We offer engaging programs designed to spark curiosity and develop skills in robotics and technology for students at all levels.
			</p>
			
			<div class="opportunity-cards">
				<div class="opportunity-card">
					<h3>Elementary</h3>
					<p>Introduction to robotics through fun, hands-on activities designed for young learners. Our elementary programs focus on creativity and basic engineering concepts.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-card">
					<h3>Middle</h3>
					<p>Intermediate robotics projects that build on foundational knowledge. Middle school students engage with more complex challenges and begin coding their own robots.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-card">
					<h3>High School</h3>
					<p>Advanced robotics and engineering opportunities for high school students. Participants work on sophisticated projects and may prepare for competitions or college-level studies.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="content-section">
			<h2>How to Get Started</h2>
			<p>Getting involved with our K-12 programs is easy! Here's what you need to know:</p>
			
			<div class="opportunity-list">
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Program Registration</h3>
					<p>Most of our programs require advance registration. Check our events calendar for upcoming dates and registration deadlines.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Parental Consent</h3>
					<p>All participants under 18 will need parental consent forms completed before joining any of our programs.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>What to Bring</h3>
					<p>Most programs provide all necessary materials, but participants should bring a notebook, pen, and enthusiasm for learning!</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="content-section">
			<h2>Success Stories</h2>
			<p>Many students who started in our K-12 programs have gone on to pursue STEM fields in college and beyond. Here are a few highlights:</p>
			
			<div class="opportunity-list">
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Regional Robotics Competition</h3>
					<p>Our high school team took first place in the regional robotics competition, qualifying for nationals.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>STEM Scholarship Winners</h3>
					<p>Three of our senior participants received full STEM scholarships to top engineering programs.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Community Impact Project</h3>
					<p>Middle school students designed and built assistive devices for local community members with disabilities.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="content-section">
			<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
			
			<div class="opportunity-list">
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Do I need prior experience?</h3>
					<p>No prior experience is necessary! Our programs are designed for all skill levels, from complete beginners to those with some robotics background.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>Are there any costs involved?</h3>
					<p>Most of our programs are free thanks to generous grants and donations. Some specialized programs may have a small materials fee.</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="opportunity-item">
					<h3>How can I prepare?</h3>
					<p>Come with an open mind and ready to learn! If you want to get a head start, we recommend exploring basic coding concepts through free online resources.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>

	<style>
		.opportunity-cards {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
			gap: 1.5rem;
			margin-top: 2rem;
		}

		.opportunity-card {
			padding: 1.5rem;
			background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.1);
			border-radius: 12px;
			border: 1px solid rgba(var(--gray), 0.1);
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
		}

		.opportunity-card:hover {
			transform: translateY(-2px);
			box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(var(--gray), 0.15);
			background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 0.15);
		}

		.opportunity-card h3 {
			margin-top: 0;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
			font-size: 1.25rem;
			color: var(--accent);
		}

		.opportunity-card p {
			margin-bottom: 0;
			font-size: 1rem;
		}

		.opportunity-list {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 1.5rem;
			margin-top: 2rem;
		}

		.opportunity-item {
			padding: 1.5rem;
			background: rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.05);
			border-radius: 12px;
			border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent), 0.1);
			transition: all 0.3s ease;
		}

		.opportunity-item:hover {
			transform: translateY(-2px);
			box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(var(--accent), 0.1);
			background: rgba(var(--accent-light), 0.1);
		}

		.opportunity-item h3 {
			margin-top: 0;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
			font-size: 1.25rem;
			color: var(--accent);
		}

		.opportunity-item p {
			margin-bottom: 0;
			font-size: 1rem;
		}

		@media (max-width: 768px) {
			.opportunity-cards {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			}
		}
	</style>
</Layout>